The paper deals with machine learning and specifically with agnostically learning halfspaces, which is a topic in computational geometry and computational learning theory. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity (cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT), which makes these categories likely as well.
